          2 Installation Procedures for the WATCOM Editor V3.5          2 Installation Procedures for the WATCOM Editor V3.5


          Step 1.  Preparation          Step 1.  Preparation

          The complete software installation process should require at most
          20 minutes.   It may be broken up  into a number of smaller steps
          which we have numbered for you (Step 1, Step 2, and so on).   You
          should  have a  number of  unused diskettes  and diskette  labels
          handy.    You  will need  one  unused  diskette for  each  WATCOM
          diskette for making backups.   If you are installing the software
          onto diskettes,  you will require,  at  most,  an equal number of
          unused diskettes for making your day-to-day working copies.

          Your personal computer should have at  least 128K bytes of memory
          in order to run the software.  You will also require a version of
          DOS which is compatible with one of IBM PC DOS versions 2.1, 3.1,
          3.2 or  3.3.   To  perform the  software installation,   you will
          require a copy of DOS and  the following DOS programs:   DISKCOPY
          and FORMAT.    These programs can be  found on the  DOS diskette.
          DOS is supplied by the manufacturer of your personal computer.


          Step 2.  Diskette BACKUP!          Step 2.  Diskette BACKUP!

          (1) The diskette  in this  package is  protected from  accidental
              erasure by a write-protect tab.   Do not remove this tab from
              the diskette.
          2                                              WATCOM Editor V3.5


 
          (2) The diskette in this package must be copied,  using DOS,  for
              backup purposes, since diskettes can be damaged by use.   You
              can use  the DOS "DISKCOPY" program  to do this  as described
              below.

          (3) Never "DISKCOPY"  onto a diskette which  contains information
              that you wish to keep.   The  disk copying process erases any
              information which might  have been on the  output diskette so
              it is best to start with a new, unused diskette.

          (4) Place a copy of your DOS diskette  in drive "A" and type in a
              DOS DISKCOPY command of the following form:

                 A>diskcopy a: b:

              Once you  have typed  in this command  and pressed  the Enter
              key, you may remove the DOS diskette.

          (5) Place the WATCOM software diskette in drive "A".

              If you have a second "B" diskette drive, place a new,  unused
              diskette  in this  drive  and proceed  as  instructed by  the
              DISKCOPY program.

              If you  do not have a  second diskette drive,   messages will
              appear, as DISKCOPY proceeds,  that will instruct you when to
              remove one diskette and insert  the other diskette into drive
              "A".   Always remember that the diskette for drive "A" is the
              WATCOM diskette and  that the diskette for drive  "B" is your
              new, unused diskette.  During the DISKCOPY operation, you may
              be required to exchange the two diskettes several times.


          Step 3.  The Software Installation Procedure          Step 3.  The Software Installation Procedure

          The WATCOM  Editor diskette contains  an "INSTALL"  program which
          can be used to install the software that it contains onto another
          diskette  or  hard  disk.   We  recommend  that  you  familiarize
          yourself with the contents of the diskette before installing them
          on  your  system.    Section 4,   entitled  "Diskette  Contents",
          describes the diskette.

          The INSTALL program is a DOS batch file which is used to copy the
          software to another diskette or to a hard disk.   It will perform
          the steps required to install the software on your system quickly
          and easily.


          Step 4.  Establishing Disk Space Requirements          Step 4.  Establishing Disk Space Requirements

          Approximately  132K bytes  of  disk space  are  required for  the
          software.
