          In the following examples,  we have  assumed that you have placed
          your backup copy of the WATCOM  diskette into diskette drive "A".
          If you are installing the software  onto another diskette and you
          do not have a second diskette drive, you must specify "B:" as the
          output location.  Messages will appear, as INSTALL proceeds, that
          will instruct  you when  to remove  one diskette  and insert  the
          other diskette into drive "A".  Always remember that the "SOURCE"
          diskette is your backup copy of  the WATCOM diskette and that the
          "TARGET" diskette  is your  new,  unused  diskette.   During  the
          installation,  you may be required  to exchange the two diskettes
          several times.

          ________          Examples:

          (1) Copy files from disk "A" to the root directory of disk "B".

                 C>a:install  a:  b:\

          (2) Copy files from disk "A" to the "CMDS" directory of disk "C".

                 C>a:install  a:  c:\cmds\

          (3) Copy files  from disk  "A" to the  current directory  of disk
              "C".

                 C>a:install  a:  c:

          Run the INSTALL program specifying parameters appropriate to your
          situation.  The INSTALL program will prompt you at various points
          to confirm the operation which it is about to perform.   You will
          be required to  type "y" (yes)  or  "n" (no)  and then  press the
          Enter key.


