          4 The WATCOM Editor Diskette          4 The WATCOM Editor Diskette

          The contents of the WATCOM Editor diskette are listed below.

          WEDIT.EXE     This is the WATCOM Editor program file.  Of all the
                        files provided with  the editor,  this is  the only
                        one which is required to run the editor.

          WEDIT.HLP     This is the editor help file.   If you wish to have
                        on-line help available while using the editor, this
                        file must  be present in  the current  directory or
                        one of the  disks or directories listed  in the DOS
                        "PATH" command.   The editor  will search disks and
                        directories  listed  in  the   DOS  "PATH"  command
                        whenever it  is unable to  locate the help  file in
                        the current directory.   The  DOS "PATH" command is
                        described in your DOS manual.

          PLAY.FTR      This is a WATCOM Editor "music" feature file.  This
                        file contains the support  for playing single-voice
                        musical notes  on just about any  personal computer
                        equipped with a speaker  and tone generator.   This
                        file  must  be  present  when  using  the  "CONFIG"
                        program to  select music support.   See  the WATCOM
                        Editor  User's Guide  for more  information on  the
                        "PLAY" command and music support.

          PLAYJR.FTR    This is a WATCOM Editor "music" feature file.  This
                        file contains  the  support for  playing  multiple-
                        voice musical  notes on the  IBM PCjr,  IBM  JX PC,
                        Tandy 1000  SX PC  or any  other personal  computer
                        equipped with  the TI76496 complex  tone generator.
                        This file must  be present when using  the "CONFIG"
                        program to  select music support.   See  the WATCOM
                        Editor  User's Guide  for more  information on  the
                        "PLAY" command and music support.

          CONFIG.COM    The "CONFIG" program may be used to modify defaults
                        in  the WATCOM  Editor and  to  select the  "music"
                        feature.  The configuration program is described in
                        the WATCOM Editor User's Guide.
