                        User's Guide  for more information on  the terminal
                        emulation program.

          CSET.COM      This program may  be used to set  screen colour and
                        mode.   You can select  the foreground,  background
                        and border  colours of personal  computers equipped
                        with  a colour  graphics  adapter.    You can  also
                        select from 80 or 40 column screen width.   Use the
                        WATCOM Editor  command "HELP  CSET" to  obtain more
                        information on the colour setting program.

          COMPRESS.EXE  The Editor will remove any  TAB characters that are
                        found in the records of  a file.   This program may
                        be used  to reinsert TAB  characters into  the file
                        and, in so doing, reduce the size of the file.  The
                        program removes strings of  blank characters from a
                        line and replaces them  with the appropriate number
                        of  TAB characters.    For  example,   8 blanks  in
                        columns 1  through 8 will  be replaced by  a single
                        TAB character.    Blanks within quoted  strings are
                        not compressed.  To use, type:

                           COMPRESS <file-specification>

                        where  <file-specification>  is a  valid  DOS  file
                        specification.   Wild card patterns such as "*.FIL"
                        may also be used with this program.  The IBM PC DOS
                        manual describes  legal wild  card patterns  in the
                        description of the DIRECTORY command.

