          5 Differences from the WATCOM Editor V3.3          5 Differences from the WATCOM Editor V3.3

          Version   3.5  of   the  WATCOM   Editor   contains  some   minor
          enhancements.

          (1)  The maximum record length that can  be handled by the editor
               has been increased from 134 to 253 characters.

          (2)  The editor  now supports  a variable  number of  screen rows
               with the EGA/VGA adapters.   The  editor recognizes when the
               number of screen rows is 25, 28, 30,  43,  or 50 and adjusts
               the editing window accordingly.

          (3)  Filenames are now treated in a case-insensitive manner.   In
               previous versions of the editor,   commands such as "edit x"
               and  "edit  X"  would  have   created  two  workspaces  with
               different names.  Now the editor will search for a workspace
               name that matches the specified  filename without regard for
               case.

          (4)  The editing profile filenames have  changed.   The new names
               are as follows:

                  Program Name  Software Product   Profile Filename
                  WBAS.EXE      WATCOM BASIC       WBAS.PRF
                  WEDITC.EXE    WATCOM C           WEDITC.PRF
